						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent"> figure its has to with $2002, but im wondering "Can i write to the PPU safely within my NMI"?</div><br />Yes, for a limited amount of time.<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Or do i have to port my PPU pokes in my main loop after my VBLANK has occurred.</div><br />It doesn't matter where the code that writes to PPU is placed, it only matters when it's executed. You can only write to PPU either it you turned rendering off (which I recommand for wirting a whole nametable) or during VBlank, which is usually done in NMI routine, but doesn't have to technically.[/quote]</div>

					
