				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Most documents refer to the lower 2 bits of $2000 as "name table selection" bits, but it really is easier to master scrolling if you think of them as the highest bits of each coordinate, and the lower 8 bits of them is what is written to $2005.
<br />
<br />So, like tepples said, there is no need at all to mess with $2006 to adjust the scrolling, as long as it's done during Vblank (to fully set the scroll outside of VBlank you have to use $2006).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
